result.execSummary:
The defendant Chelsey Lynn Ninham-Thomas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to obtain and maintain full time employment, unless medically excused by a treating physician.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No contact with D. Thiel directly or indirectly. No phone calls, e-mails, text messages, written communications or by third party.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  Defendant to comply with any counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Case called @ 2:58 p.m. Defendant Chelsey Lynn Ninham-Thomas in court with attorney Amanda Belville. DE appears via video. Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives right to appear in person for the hearing.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Cts 1 & 2 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Statement by DE. Court orders: S/W 2 years probation - Conditions: NC w/ D. Thiel, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, Counseling/treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent, Maintain full time, gainful employment, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court. 5 days CFTS. Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights faxed to the jail.
